other_tests.findings: Lesion of intermediate density along the anterior margin of the left lateral segments of the liver measuring 17 mm, probable hemangioma; hypodense lesion measuring 19 mm along the posterior right lobe of the liver that may also represent a hemangioma but is not well characterized; small angiomyolipoma in the right kidney measuring up to 18 mm; fluid collection in the right lower quadrant measuring up to 37 x 33 mm containing air and fluid, with a direct communication between the dilated appendiceal tip and the collection; small bowel wall thickening in the area explained by associated regional peritonitis; slight reactive bladder wall thickening; atherosclerotic changes moderate; moderate compression deformity of the L2 vertebral body likely chronic; moderate to severe degenerative changes of the lumbar spine.
